args:
The party succeeds in freeing Wu Kong from
the Jin Gu Er's thrall. Feeling that her lack of
belief in Wu Kong was the cause of all their
troubles, Xuan Zang swears to have faith
in the future from that point on. Afterward,
the group finally arrives at the Qilin village.
*pant* *pant* Looks like...we've made it...\nall the way up.
Based on what Xuan Zang told us,\nwe oughta be there any time.
Are you still with us, Cleo?
I'm here.\nAt least this was easier than last time.
Yep. Though a certain someone has it that\nmuch worse...
What the heck is in this thing?!\nAnd how is it SO heavy?!
For one who wishes to become a sealer,\nit worries me to hear you ask that.
Your burden is the power of one of the\nQilin relics I have entrusted you with.\nTake a guess as to which one.
Uh...is it the Huang Jin Sheng?
Incorrect. Such wild guesses will only\nearn you further punishment.
Indeed. Now, if you don't answer quickly—\nand correctly, of course—the load will\nonly continue to grow.
Oh, come on! Okay, so I guess it's...\nuh...the Ba Jiao Shan?
I was unaware the Ba Jiao Shan had the\npower to do this sort of thing.
Ha ha! Looks like that kid's got his\nwork cut out for him.
I know it seems nine kinds'a cruel,\nbut she's actually doin' him a favor.
Indeed. Enduring a strict punishment will\nhelp him meet his master's gaze again\nthat much more quickly.
Still, I AM surprised that all of our bags\ncan fit inside one small little jar.
It is a new wonder every day when it\ncomes to those Qilin relics.
She said it can even make stuff feel light,\nno matter how much is in there!
Wish my stomach could do that...
I suppose there would have been a\npreponderance of such relics in the\nera of the ancient Qilin.
Maybe that's the reason for it all.
What do you mean by ＂it all＂?
Remember what Xuan Zang said about\nthe ancient Qilin meeting with ruin?

Maybe that was because they lived in a
world full of things everyone wanted,
and people couldn't bear the notion of
not possessing all of it.
Well, THAT'S a grim thought.\nYou really think it's true?
Notte, say there was a bag that could\nproduce an unlimited amount of cake.\nWould you not desire it?
Are you kidding me? I'd shove an old lady\nin the mud to get a magic cake bag!

But let's say this theoretical bag cannot
produce anything BUT cake. What, then,
do you think would happen if you were
to find a bag that could make cookies?
OUTTA THE WAY, GRANNY!\nGIMME THAT BAG!
That's 'cause there ain't no limit to desire.\nIt's tough to be satisfied with what ya got.
Huh. I figured the ancient Qilin would\nbe better than that, but maybe not.
No matter how much secret, mysterious\nknowledge they might have had, they\nwere likely just like us deep down.
That might be part'a why all the modern\nQilin don't come out all that much.
Right. If people with that much power\nspent time in the human world, we might\ncome to rely too much on them.
So instead, they hide themselves away\nand send sealers out into the world to\nundo the damage of their ancestors.
It is no easy thing to own one's mistakes.\nAs such, I find their spirit more impressive\nthan their technology or knowledge.
They know and accept their past,\nand also try to learn from it.
They're an impressive bunch, all right.\nPlus they get REALLY scary if you\never get 'em mad!
I wish to thank you. Had you not been\nhere, I would not have freed Wu Kong.
I think you had much more to do with it.\nYou're the sealer, after all.
And yet, I was ready to surrender my\npupil's life until you taught me to\nhave faith in the future.
Is that why you're being so harsh\non Wu Kong now?
I wanted to have more faith in him.
I believe he will someday be a sealer\nwho far surpasses me, which will drive\nall worries far from my mind.
So I am trying to believe in his talent—\nand his future.
Of course! After all, the most important\naspect of Wu Kong's development\nis his wonderful teacher.
You have to believe you're the one who\ncan guide him on the proper path.
And here I thought you were finished\nteaching me lessons.
Very well. As you suggest, I will believe\nin myself and my future, as well as his.
And now, my friends...we have arrived.
I can't wait to see all the secrets it holds!
